{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "DigitalDrift",
  "description": "Digital Drift — a faithful node-graph rebuild of the Latent Space website background mosh, reconstructed from composable atoms (no wgsl_compute monolith). The website's single fragment pass decomposes into three contributions that all sum into one UV offset and resample the source once, exactly as the original does: (1) the per-band horizontal slide is node.scanline_jitter_field in its new Slide motion (smooth value-noise drift, every band, ungated — band count = `bands`), emitting a signed R offset; (2) the organic domain-warp flow is built from atoms — system.generator_input.time → two node.math (Multiply by +0.13 / -0.13) produce the website's t = u_time*0.13 and -t, fed into two node.noise nodes in the new Value type (the 123.34/456.21/45.32 value-noise hash) sampled at uv*3 ± t, packed R/G by node.pack_channels and re-ranged to a signed UV offset by node.scale_offset_texture(scale 0.028, offset -0.014) = (value_noise - 0.5)*0.028; (3) node.mix(Add) sums the flow offset (RG) and the slide offset (R), and node.remap(Relative) warps the source by the summed field in a single resample. The RGB fringe at the seams is node.radial_offset_field(Linear, angle 0) → node.chromatic_displace, the horizontal channel split. A final node.mix(Lerp, amount) crossfades the whole effect back over the untouched source so Drift=0 is a clean passthrough (skipMode onZero). node.value fans the master Drift to both the slide amount and the final crossfade. The value-noise field is the literal website function — the Value type on node.noise and the matching hash on node.scanline_jitter_field's Slide mode both carry the same 123.34/456.21/45.32 constants — so this is the actual effect, not a lookalike. Documented divergences vs the website: (a) the warp + slide resample once after summing (the website also samples once); the chromatic split is a separate post pass on the warped image (a tiny extra bilinear tap, visually negligible) rather than folded into the same fetch; (b) the website's occasional glitch-gate `g` (smoothstep-gated big shift + g-scaled chromatic) is omitted — Digital Drift is the calm continuous form; add a second node.scanline_jitter_field in Tear mode for the spiky accent; (c) source UVs are canvas [0,1] (the clip already fills the canvas) rather than the website's aspect-cover branch. Time comes from system.generator_input.time (flow) and FrameTime.seconds (the slide reads it internally).",
  "presetMetadata": {
    "id": "DigitalDrift",
    "displayName": "Digital Drift",
    "category": "Filmic",
    "oscPrefix": "digitaldrift",
    "available": true,
    "params": [
